--- Thread (2 messages, 2020-12-01) ---
[2020-12-01 12:58] velizar_ (Name): continued from #ask_a_dev: are 1ls cryo rays strictly worse than gauss charges in the situation where you have no freeze units already? You have x attack, you choose between gaining y attack vs gaining y 1ls cryo rays
[2020-12-01 12:58] velizar_ (Name): if x+y attack is enough to breach, then with y freeze you would only freeze some units instead of killing them;

--- Thread (2 messages, 2020-12-01) ---
[2020-12-01 13:28] velizar_ (Name): if you freeze the absorber and that uses up all your freeze, then you gave y freeze to deny y - 1 or less absorb, so in that case the gauss charges are better;
freezing multiple absorbers gains nothing over freezing a single absorber, so it's never better than gauss charges for that amount;
after you've frozen the absorber and not intending to freeze any other absorbers (because of the previous statement), you can only freeze soak, but we've already proven that that is not as good as gauss charges.
[2020-12-01 13:28] velizar_ (Name): I think that concludes the proof

